message.entry: Supports word lengths less than or equal to 16 bits.
Supports word lengths less than or equal to 32 bits.
This data type is supported at the output port(s).
This data type is supported at the input port(s).
The blocks inside the subsystem dictate the data types supported by this block.
The output port supports 32-bit signed integers only. Input ports Theta and Rho support signed integers, while Ref1 supports signed and unsigned integers.
Input ports Theta and Rho support signed fixed-point data types with word lengths less than or equal to 32, while Ref1 supports signed and unsigned fixed-point data types.
This data type is only supported at the input port Ref1.
This data type is not supported for the <tt>Local Intensity Comparison</tt> method.
Fixed-point data types are not supported at the Major Axis, Minor Axis, Orientation, and Eccentricity output ports.
Code generation not suitable for fixed-point processors.
Generated code will be restricted to MATLAB host computers when you set the FFT implementation parameter to FFTW, or when the transform length is not a power of two.
